{"id":8550,"date":"2025-09-22T10:43:44","date_gmt":"2025-09-22T10:43:44","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/realtrips.in\/?post_type=trip&#038;p=8550"},"modified":"2025-11-27T11:33:07","modified_gmt":"2025-11-27T11:33:07","slug":"goa","status":"publish","type":"trip","link":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/trip\/goa\/","title":{"rendered":"GOA"},"content":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":8838,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","template":"","destination":[102],"activities":[],"trip_types":[75],"difficulty":[],"trip_tag":[],"wptravelengine_custom_taxonomy_tripcategory":[77],"class_list":["post-8550","trip","type-trip","status-publish","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","destination-short-break-goa","trip_types-customized-domestic-tour","tripcategory-customized-domestic-tour"],"packages_ids":[8551],"trip_extras":[],"cut_off_time":{"enabled":false,"duration":0,"duration_unit":"days"},"booked-seats":[],"code":"WTE-8550","price":11777,"has_sale":false,"sale_price":0,"discount_percent":0,"currency":{"code":"INR","symbol":"&#8377;"},"duration":{"days":4,"nights":3,"duration_unit":"days","duration_type":"days"},"min_pax":1,"max_pax":"","discount_value":0,"discount_label":"&#8377;0 Off","primary_category":27,"available_times":{"type":"default","items":["2021-1-01","2021-2-01","2021-3-01","2021-4-01","2021-5-01","2021-6-01","2021-7-01","2021-8-01","2021-9-01","2021-10-01","2021-11-01","2021-12-01"]},"description":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Take a perfect short escape to <strong>Goa<\/strong>, where golden beaches, vibrant nightlife, and rich heritage create an unforgettable holiday. Spend your days relaxing on lively North Goa beaches like <strong>Calangute, Baga, and Anjuna<\/strong>, or enjoy the calm charm of South Goa\u2019s <strong>Palolem and Colva<\/strong>. Explore the <strong>UNESCO-listed churches of Old Goa<\/strong>, colorful markets, and Portuguese-style streets that showcase the state\u2019s colonial past. For adventure seekers, Goa offers thrilling <strong>water sports<\/strong>, dolphin cruises, and island trips, while evenings come alive with music, shacks, and beach parties. Whether you\u2019re looking for leisure, culture, or adventure, Goa is the ultimate destination for a short yet exciting break.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->","cost_includes":"3 star premium hotel stay\n All transfers and sightseeing by AC Vehicle\n This cost valid for 6 adults traveling together\n Breakfast, Dinner\n Toll Tax\n Parking\n Driver Allowance\nTravel Goodies\n 24 x 7 On tour Assistance\n All cost from EX Destination","cost_excludes":" Any meals other than those mentioned above in inclusions\n Airfare \/ Train Ticket\n GST 5%\n All monument entry Fees\n Any portage at airports and hotels, tips, insurance, wine, mineral water, telephone charges, and all items of personal nature\n Any services not specifically mentioned in the inclusions\nEntrance fees to Monuments & other sightseeing points\nExpenses caused by factors beyond our control like rail and flight delays, roadblocks, vehicle malfunctions, political disturbances, etc.\nAnything not mentioned in inclusions","itineraries":[],"faqs":[{"title":"1. What is the ideal duration for a short Goa trip?","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A 3 to 4-day trip is perfect to enjoy the beaches, heritage sites, and nightlife.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"2. Which are the must-visit beaches in Goa? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Popular ones include Calangute, Baga, Anjuna, Vagator (North Goa) and Colva, Palolem, Agonda (South Goa).<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"3. What are the main attractions apart from beaches? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Old Goa churches (Basilica of Bom Jesus, Se Cathedral), Fort Aguada, Chapora Fort, spice plantations, flea markets, and river cruises.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"4. What kind of activities can I enjoy in Goa? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Water sports (parasailing, banana boat rides, scuba diving), dolphin watching, island trips, shopping, and nightlife experiences.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"9. How do I get around in Goa? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tourists often rent scooters, bikes, or cars for convenience. Taxis and auto-rickshaws are also available.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"}],"is_featured":false,"featured_image":{"width":374,"height":226,"file":"2025\/09\/goa-1.png","filesize":178152,"sizes":{"medium":{"file":"goa-1-300x181.png","width":300,"height":181,"filesize":38014,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/goa-1-300x181.png"},"thumbnail":{"file":"goa-1-150x150.png","width":150,"height":150,"filesize":36308,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/goa-1-150x150.png"},"blog-sidebar-size":{"file":"goa-1-100x100.png","width":100,"height":100,"filesize":18618,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/goa-1-100x100.png"},"blog-sidebar-size-thumb":{"file":"goa-1-90x80.png","width":90,"height":80,"filesize":7473,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/goa-1-90x80.png"},"blog-post-two":{"file":"goa-1-342x226.png","width":342,"height":226,"filesize":111131,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/goa-1-342x226.png"},"travolo-related-post-size":{"file":"goa-1-270x226.png","width":270,"height":226,"filesize":91896,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/goa-1-270x226.png"},"blog-post-pagination":{"file":"goa-1-80x80.png","width":80,"height":80,"filesize":6817,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/up